Attack on RSA
We can identify three approaches to attacking RSA 
mathematically:
1.  Factor n into its two prime factors. This enables calculation 
of ø(n) = (p – 1) x (q– 1), which in turn enables determination 
of d = e-1 (mod ø(n))
2.  Determine ø(n) directly without first determining p and q. 
Again this enables determination of d = e-1 (mod ø(n))
3.  Determine d directly without first determining ø(n)
